Sentencas: In this study, micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells (MT-SOFCs) were manufactured by successive electrophoretic deposition (EPD) in non-aqueous solvent.
Titulo: Characterization of anode supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells prepared by successive non-aqueous electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: At first, stable suspensions of YSZ (Electrolyte), Ni/YSZ (anode) and LSM (cathode) in isopropanol were prepared.
Titulo: Characterization of anode supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells prepared by successive non-aqueous electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: The EPD was performed on graphite rods under various voltages and times.
Titulo: Characterization of anode supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells prepared by successive non-aqueous electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: The proper EPD condition was determined to prepare porous electrodes and dense electrolyte layers.
Titulo: Characterization of anode supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells prepared by successive non-aqueous electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: The graphite rod was decomposed by heating at 900C and the resulting tubular thin films were sintered in air at 1350C.
Titulo: Characterization of anode supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells prepared by successive non-aqueous electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: The microstructure of the sintered samples was studied by SEM analysis.
Titulo: Characterization of anode supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells prepared by successive non-aqueous electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: The performance of the SOFC was investigated by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Characterization of anode supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells prepared by successive non-aqueous electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: It was found that MT-SOFC with an internal diameter of 0.7 mm can be obtained via successive EPD.
Titulo: Characterization of anode supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells prepared by successive non-aqueous electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the cell was 0.25 W/cm(2)at 850C.
Titulo: Characterization of anode supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells prepared by successive non-aqueous electrophoretic deposition
